<div class="security-education-module rounded-lg bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 shadow-md p-6">
  <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Understanding Security Alerts</h2>
  
  <div class="mb-6">
    <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
      Our app uses advanced security systems to monitor your account for suspicious activity. When potential security issues are detected, you'll receive alerts through the app and other channels based on your notification preferences.
    </p>
  </div>
  
  <div class="space-y-6">
    <!-- Alert Type: Critical -->
    <div class="alert-type-card border-l-4 border-red-500 bg-red-50 dark:bg-red-900/20 p-4 rounded-r-lg">
      <h3 class="flex items-center text-lg font-medium text-red-800 dark:text-red-300 mb-2">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-red-600 dark:text-red-400 mr-2" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z" />
        </svg>
        Critical Security Alerts
      </h3>
      <p class="text-red-700 dark:text-red-300 mb-2">
        These alerts require your immediate attention as they indicate a serious security concern.
      </p>
      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded p-3 mb-3">
        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Examples include:</h4>
        <ul class="ml-6 list-disc text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mt-2">
          <li>Multiple failed login attempts</li>
          <li>Password changes you didn't initiate</li>
          <li>Unusual high-value transactions</li>
          <li>Account access from suspicious locations</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-red-700 dark:text-red-300">
        <strong>Action required:</strong> Review the alert details and contact support immediately if you don't recognize the activity.
      </p>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Alert Type: Warning -->
    <div class="alert-type-card border-l-4 border-yellow-500 bg-yellow-50 dark:bg-yellow-900/20 p-4 rounded-r-lg">
      <h3 class="flex items-center text-lg font-medium text-yellow-800 dark:text-yellow-300 mb-2">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-yellow-600 dark:text-yellow-400 mr-2" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z" />
        </svg>
        Warning Alerts
      </h3>
      <p class="text-yellow-700 dark:text-yellow-300 mb-2">
        These alerts highlight potentially suspicious activity that requires your attention.
      </p>
      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded p-3 mb-3">
        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Examples include:</h4>
        <ul class="ml-6 list-disc text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mt-2">
          <li>Login from a new device</li>
          <li>Transactions in unusual locations</li>
          <li>Transactions outside your normal patterns</li>
          <li>Changes to account settings</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-yellow-700 dark:text-yellow-300">
        <strong>Action required:</strong> Review the alert and confirm if the activity was authorized by you.
      </p>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Alert Type: Information -->
    <div class="alert-type-card border-l-4 border-blue-500 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-900/20 p-4 rounded-r-lg">
      <h3 class="flex items-center text-lg font-medium text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 mb-2">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 mr-2" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
        </svg>
        Information Alerts
      </h3>
      <p class="text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-300 mb-2">
        These alerts provide important security information about your account.
      </p>
      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded p-3 mb-3">
        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Examples include:</h4>
        <ul class="ml-6 list-disc text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mt-2">
          <li>Successful logins to your account</li>
          <li>Security settings changes you initiated</li>
          <li>Security tips and recommendations</li>
          <li>Reminders to update your security settings</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-300">
        <strong>Action required:</strong> No immediate action needed, but review the information to stay informed.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="mt-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">How Our Security Alert System Works</h3>
    
    <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-700 rounded-lg p-4 space-y-4">
      <div class="flex">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-primary-100 dark:bg-primary-800 flex items-center justify-center text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 mr-3">
          <span class="font-bold">1</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Continuous Monitoring</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            Our system continuously monitors your account activity for patterns that might indicate security risks.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="flex">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-primary-100 dark:bg-primary-800 flex items-center justify-center text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 mr-3">
          <span class="font-bold">2</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Risk Assessment</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            When unusual activity is detected, our system analyzes the risk level based on multiple factors, including your usual behavior patterns.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="flex">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-primary-100 dark:bg-primary-800 flex items-center justify-center text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 mr-3">
          <span class="font-bold">3</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Intelligent Alerts</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            If a potential security risk is identified, you'll receive alerts through the app, email, or SMS, depending on the severity and your notification preferences.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="flex">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-primary-100 dark:bg-primary-800 flex items-center justify-center text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 mr-3">
          <span class="font-bold">4</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Protective Actions</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            For high-risk activities, our system may automatically take protective measures, such as blocking suspicious transactions or requiring additional verification.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="mt-8 p-4 bg-green-50 dark:bg-green-900/20 rounded-lg border border-green-200 dark:border-green-800">
    <h3 class="flex items-center text-lg font-medium text-green-800 dark:text-green-300 mb-2">
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-green-600 dark:text-green-400 mr-2" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z" />
      </svg>
      Customize Your Security Notifications
    </h3>
    <p class="text-green-700 dark:text-green-300 mb-4">
      You can customize how you receive security alerts in your notification preferences. We recommend enabling all security notifications to stay fully protected.
    </p>
    <a href="/settings/notifications" class="inline-flex items-center px-4 py-2 border border-transparent text-sm font-medium rounded-md shadow-sm text-white bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-offset-2 focus:ring-green-500">
      Update Notification Settings
    </a>
  </div>
</div>